OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCost of living: Energy     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbills to rise 14 times     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffaster than wages, says TUC
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Energy bills are due to rise at least  
OL,6, 14 times faster than wages this year,  
OL,7, new research by the Trades Union       
OL,8, Congress (TUC) suggests.               
OL,10,FThe TUC said average weekly wages are  
OL,11,Fdue to rise by 3.75% - while the price 
OL,12,Fcap for gas and electricity set by     
OL,13,FOfgem will go up by 54% in April.      
OL,15,FThat means energy price rises alone    
OL,16,Fcould wipe out or exceed pay rises.    
OL,18,FThe government says it is offering     
OL,19,F#21bn of help with bills - but rejected
OL,20,Fhalting a rise in National Insurance.  
